Ayen Enerji AS (AYEN) , a Turkish utility,
fell in Istanbul after it was beaten an auction for a stake in
an electricity distribution grid.  The shares dropped 3.1 percent to 1.55 liras at the close
in Istanbul, the biggest decline since March 29.  Yonca Enerji won the auction for a 20 percent stake in the
electricity grid in the central province of Kayseri, with a bid
of $16.05 million, the governmentâ€™s asset sales agency said
